# CARL List Build Domain
# =======================
# Triggers when Oliver mentions list building, CSV management, lead enrichment,
# LinkedIn post scraping, or any step in the Apify/Prospeo/ZeroBounce/Instantly pipeline.
# Compacted 2026-03-19: 10 → 9 rules. Retired meta-description (routing in manifest).
# Compacted 2026-03-20: 9 → 8 rules. Merged pipeline context loading (→ CORE_LOAD_SKILLS).
#
# Format: {DOMAIN}_RULE_{N}=rule text
# Skills & pipeline context: see CORE_LOAD_SKILLS in .carl/global
# Credit gate: see CREDIT_GATE_RULE in .carl/global

# Step 0: LinkedIn post commenter scraping (Apify)
LISTBUILD_RULE_0=If Oliver wants to scrape commenters from a LinkedIn post, use Apify MCP (connected via Cowork connector). Use no-cookie actors for safety (~$2/1k comments). Output CSV to Leads/wip/[campaign-name]/. This replaces PhantomBuster for comment scraping — cheaper and no LinkedIn ban risk. After scraping, proceed to Step 1 to run the CSV through the enrichment pipeline.

# Step 1: Enforce folder conventions
LISTBUILD_RULE_1=All lead files go to the correct subfolder — NEVER to Downloads or Desktop. Raw imports → Leads/wip/[campaign-name]/. Prospeo-ready CSVs → Leads/enriched/. ZeroBounce results → Leads/enriched/batchN_zerobounce/. Valid emails for Instantly → Leads/enriched/batchN_zerobounce/valid.csv. If any file is in the wrong location, move it immediately and log the correction.

# Step 2: Credit tracking
LISTBUILD_RULE_2=Track API credits after every enrichment action. Prospeo: 1 credit per email search. Update the count in startup-brief.md after each batch. Before running a batch, calculate how many credits it will use and confirm there are enough remaining. Current balance is in startup-brief.md under "Credits". Never burn credits on contacts that already have verified emails in Apollo. (See also CREDIT_GATE_RULE in .carl/global for the 50-credit approval gate.)

# Step 3: ICP scoring before enrichment
# NotebookLM queries: see brain/notebooklm-queries.md (List Build section) | tier system: .claude/skills/notebooklm/SKILL.md
LISTBUILD_RULE_3=Before enriching a batch, score prospects against ICP criteria from "Sales Playbooks/prospecting-instructions.txt". Query ICP Signals notebook (see brain/notebooklm-queries.md). Prioritize enrichment for high-ICP-score contacts first to maximize credit efficiency.

# Step 4: Deduplication
LISTBUILD_RULE_4=Before uploading any batch to Prospeo, check for duplicates against: (a) Previously enriched batches in Leads/enriched/. (b) Apollo contacts already in the system (apollo_contacts_search). (c) Brain prospect notes. Never enrich a contact we already have data on.

# Step 5: Pipeline status tracking
LISTBUILD_RULE_5=After any pipeline action, update Leads/STATUS.md with: which batch was processed, how many valid/invalid/catch-all, credits used, and next step. Also update startup-brief.md pipeline section if a campaign progressed.

# Step 6: Feed ICP Signals notebook
# NotebookLM feed command: see brain/notebooklm-queries.md (List Build section)
LISTBUILD_RULE_6=After processing a batch through ZeroBounce, feed the results into the ICP Signals notebook (see brain/notebooklm-queries.md for command). Save a summary of which prospect types had valid vs invalid emails, which industries had the best hit rate, and any patterns observed.

# Step 7: Google Sheets integration (via Rube MCP)
LISTBUILD_RULE_7=When Google Sheets is available (Rube MCP connected), use it as the live tracking layer: (a) Apify scrape output goes directly into a campaign Sheet instead of just a local CSV. (b) Each campaign gets one Sheet with tabs: Raw Commenters | ICP Scored | Enriched | Verified | Sent | Replied. (c) Update enrichment status per row as leads move through the pipeline. (d) Track credit usage in a Credits tab. This replaces CSV-juggling with a single live view Oliver can check from his phone.

# Step 8: Ad platform signal detection (FREE — runs after Step 4, before Step 5)
LISTBUILD_RULE_8=After post-enrichment scoring (Step 4), scan each surviving lead's company_domain for ad platform signals (Meta Pixel, Google Ads tag, GTM, Klaviyo, Shopify). This is FREE (website fetch only, no API credits). Add columns: meta_pixel, google_ads, ad_platforms, likely_budget_tier, top_roas_gap. Use domain/reference/meta-api-patterns.md and domain/reference/google-ads-patterns.md inference tables. If domain missing or scan fails, infer from industry + company_size. These columns power personalized cold email angles and demo prep. See lead-filtering-sop.md Step 4b for full detection spec.
